WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.480
[Amit Varma]: One of the common certitudes of our species is that we know the world that we live in.

00:00:10.480 --> 00:00:14.600
[Amit Varma]: I would argue that not only do we not know it, we don't even see it.

00:00:14.600 --> 00:00:19.880
[Amit Varma]: All of us exist in a bubble of our own, surrounded by infinite invisible worlds.

00:00:19.880 --> 00:00:24.000
[Amit Varma]: If we are in a car in a traffic jam, the beggar at the signal or the hawkers on the pavement

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:28.120
[Amit Varma]: may be invisible to us, the waiters at the restaurants we dine at, the domestic help

00:00:28.120 --> 00:00:31.320
[Amit Varma]: around us, the building watchmen, all invisible.

00:00:31.320 --> 00:00:36.640
[Amit Varma]: If we are men, we do not see the extra layer of awareness all women carry, such as when

00:00:36.640 --> 00:00:40.760
[Amit Varma]: a stranger walks in their direction on the footpath or when they enter a lift filled

00:00:40.760 --> 00:00:42.040
[Amit Varma]: with other people.

00:00:42.040 --> 00:00:46.960
[Amit Varma]: The exact construction of our bubble changes from moment to moment, but there are always

00:00:46.960 --> 00:00:51.760
[Amit Varma]: things we do not see, and often things we choose not to see.

00:00:51.760 --> 00:00:56.780
[Amit Varma]: Defining ourselves by identities of happenstance, we divide the world into categories based

00:00:56.780 --> 00:01:00.880
[Amit Varma]: on class, religion, caste, gender, nationality, and so on.

00:01:00.880 --> 00:01:06.000
[Amit Varma]: We wear these identities like straight jackets, restricting ourselves and the better angels

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:07.000
[Amit Varma]: of our nature.

00:01:07.000 --> 00:01:13.160
[Amit Varma]: But one thing that can temporarily make us forget these barriers we have built is art.

00:01:13.160 --> 00:01:17.880
[Amit Varma]: We can all be transported by a beautiful image or get lost in a piece of music, and then

00:01:17.880 --> 00:01:20.360
[Amit Varma]: the divisions between us don't matter.

00:01:20.360 --> 00:01:23.440
[Amit Varma]: But even that art may be shaped by those divisions.

00:01:23.440 --> 00:01:29.200
[Amit Varma]: And in any case, when the music stops, we are back to being our narrow parochial selves.

00:01:29.200 --> 00:01:35.560
[Amit Varma]: It is a rare artist who, even after the song is over, can continue to peel back the layers

00:01:35.560 --> 00:01:36.560
[Amit Varma]: of the unseen.

