00:01:52.800 --> 00:01:57.560
[Amit Varma]: My guest today is a remarkable TM Krishna, who is not just a legend of the Carnatic music

00:01:57.560 --> 00:02:03.440
[Amit Varma]: world, but also a fearless public intellectual who has spoken out repeatedly over the years

00:02:03.440 --> 00:02:09.040
[Amit Varma]: against the very structures of power that he himself benefited from, the orthodoxies

00:02:09.040 --> 00:02:11.120
[Amit Varma]: of Brahmanism and patriarchy.

00:02:11.120 --> 00:02:16.960
[Amit Varma]: TM has written numerous books, most recently Sebastian and Sons, and is arguably one of

00:02:16.960 --> 00:02:22.480
[Amit Varma]: India's most powerful voices today, in the context of his art, an uplifting voice, and

00:02:22.480 --> 00:02:25.880
[Amit Varma]: in the context of his politics, a discordant voice.

00:02:25.880 --> 00:02:29.240
